definition: (used for transliteration)/old variant of 謳|讴[ou1]
Europe/abbr. for 歐洲|欧洲[Ou1 zhou1]/surname Ou
Ba state during Zhou dynasty (in east of modern Sichuan)/abbr. for east Sichuan or Chongqing/surname Ba/abbr. for Palestine or Palestinian/abbr. for Pakistan

to long for/to wish/to cling to/to stick to/sth that sticks/close to/next to/spread open/informal abbr. for bus 巴士[ba1 shi4]/bar (unit of pressure)/nominalizing suffix on certain nouns, such as 尾巴[wei3 ba5], tail
Europe/abbr. to 歐洲|欧洲[Ou1 zhou1]

sentences.english: France is one of the member states of the ELL.
sentences.chinese: 法國事歐羅巴洲同盟成員國之一。

sentences.english: King Agenor had a pretty daughter called Europa.
sentences.chinese: 國王阿革諾耳有一個美麗的女兒叫歐羅巴。

sentences.english: The Europa imitates a Buddha positive pain and sufferings but brave of face dashing billow.
sentences.chinese: 歐羅巴彷彿正痛苦但勇敢的面對着洶湧的巨浪。

sentences.english: Do the deposits on Europa also contain elemental sulfur?
sentences.chinese: 那麼歐羅巴上的沉積物中也有單質硫嗎？

sentences.english: Clotho took this skirt to Zeus and suggested Europa to him.
sentences.chinese: 克羅託把這件衣服要過來，讓宙斯去送給歐羅巴。

sentences.english: The lanky Europe, cannot stop our Kingdom of Heaven's gold armored soldiers and iron horses.
sentences.chinese: 瘦瘦的歐羅巴，擋不住天朝的金戈鐵馬。

sentences.english: “European Gottlieb” means the place of the sun set, namely the west from which the name of Asia and Europe is transferred.
sentences.chinese: 亞細亞洲和歐羅巴洲的名稱，就是由此轉化而來。

definition: to come back to one's hometown in silken robes (idiom); to return in glory
